        "A. Large-scale systematic monitoring of public areas using automated decision-making"
      ],
      "correct": 3,
      "justification_correct": "GDPR Article 35 mandates DPIA for high-risk processing, including systematic monitoring and automated decision-making. ISO 27701:2019 aligns with this requirement, emphasizing assessment of processing activities that could significantly impact data subjects' rights.",
      "justification_wrong": "Employee count exemptions and routine processing do not trigger mandatory DPIA under GDPR Article 35. Low-risk marketing data collection does not meet the threshold for mandatory impact assessment under normative privacy frameworks."
    },
    {
      "num": 12,
      "text": "Which privacy framework specifically addresses Privacy by Design principles as a foundational control mechanism?",
